cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR

This paper deals with interference management in cognitive radio networks, which involves signal processing, network protocols, and system design. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the transmission, processing, and utilization of information. The paper also involves network infrastructure and communication protocols, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper proposes power control algorithms, which involves system design and optimization, and hence falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also involves mathematical modeling and optimization, which falls under cs.MM (Mathematical Modeling). Finally, the paper deals with cognitive radio networks, which falls under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
